item.title: Skizz
item.dc:creator: @goatee goatee
item.description:
@goatee wrote:

Fightme - the introduction was really good but then it just like… died. I wanted it to get louder afterwards. Good beat, really changes the mood of things. Probably tweaks the mood very well when high. Really good one.

Peace - Nice unpredictable beat. That and the notes reminded me of some slow jazz.

OneZero - Really good imagery in this one. You conducted effective disorientation with the sound and it gave me a sense of fear and confusion. I liked it ;).

I think you came up with some really good stuff in these and they are like “snippets of mood and setting”. Good work.

item.title: Skizz
item.dc:creator: @goatee goatee
item.description:
@goatee wrote:

Ill download

EDIT: I’m listening to them and they are pretty cool but what i really don’t like is the pauses between “verses” … it just breaks up the track for me its not too pleasant to listen to.

I’d rather you just kept to the same “type” of music per track instead of trying to blend into eachother because after you noticed it’s changed it’s not too nice to listen to.

Good work though.

item.title: Skizz
item.dc:creator: @PaulT PaulT
item.description:
@PaulT wrote:

goatee:

Did you make new tracks by remixing two songs?

Yeah, it’s really more deathno than anything else. Deathno is a genre I invented five seconds ago to describe my music. It is punk rock clips mixed with techno mixed with death metal. I don’t fucking know.

It’s just mad trippy shit.

It doesn’t sound like anything else.

It doesn’t sound like some shit made in Garage Band by a fifth grader.
